ok it to himself to do what Reed did not dare to do, and kill Doom.</li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/TheUltimates" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/TheUltimates">The Ultimates</a></em>: The Ultimates recruit Quicksilver and the Scarlet Witch, from the Brotherhood of Mutant Supremacy. Nick Fury points that this is not the first that the security services made deals with terrorists.</li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/UltimateXMen" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/UltimateXMen">Ultimate X-Men</a></em>: Xavier loathes mutants taking advantage of their superior powers to impose their will of regular humans, no matter the circumstances. Wolverine, on the other hand, has no problem making a display of his powers to a mafia boss so he accepts to leave Colossus alone.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BadassInDistress" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BadassInDistress">Badass in Distress</a><ul><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/TheUltimates" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/TheUltimates">The Ultimates</a></em><ul><li> Hulk is gaining the upper hand on Captain America, just in time for Thor to make his entrance.</li><li> Hawkeye manages to escape the blast of the Chitauri bomb at the office building, but now he's clinging from debris, with another soldier in his other hand, and four Chitauri about to shoot him. Black Widow made a super window jump, got the gun thrown from a helicopter above, and shot down the Chitauri, saving Hawkeye.</li><li> The Wasp, under medical care after Pym's wifebeating incident, did not join the Ultimates in Micronesia and stayed at the base. She was captured by the Chitauri when they made their move, so Black Widow had to rescue her when the team got back.</li></ul></li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/UltimateFF" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/UltimateFF">Ultimate FF</a